locations.description:
An attack that misses by 1 hits the torso instead. Only
impaling (imp), piercing (pi-, pi, pi+, pi++), and
tight-beam burning (burn) attacks can target the eye – and
only from the front or sides. Injury over HP÷10 blinds the
eye. Otherwise, treat as skull, but without the extra DR!

An attack that misses by 1 hits the torso instead. Wounding
modifier is x4. Knockdown rolls are at -10. Critical hits
use the Critical Head Blow Table (B556). Exception: These
special effects do not apply to toxic (tox) damage.

An attack that misses by 1 hits the torso instead. Jaw,
cheeks, nose, ears, etc. If the target has an open-faced
helmet, ignore its DR. Knockdown rolls are at -5. Critical
hits use the Critical Head Blow Table (B556). Corrosion
(cor) damage gets a x1½ wounding modifier, and if it
inflicts a major wound, it also blinds one eye (both eyes on
damage over full HP). Random attacks from behind hit the
skull instead.

Reduce the wounding multiplier of large piercing (pi+), huge
piercing (pi++), and impaling (imp) damage to x1. Any major
wound (loss of over ½ HP from one blow) cripples the limb.
Damage beyond that threshold is lost.

Reduce the wounding multiplier of large piercing (pi+), huge
piercing (pi++), and impaling (imp) damage to x1. Any major
wound (loss of over ½ HP from one blow) cripples the limb.
Damage beyond that threshold is lost. If holding a shield,
double the penalty to hit: -4 for shield arm instead of -2.

An attack that misses by 1 hits the torso instead. Human
males and the males of similar species suffer double shock
from crushing (cr) damage, and get -5 to knockdown rolls.
Otherwise, treat as a torso hit.

Reduce the wounding multiplier of large piercing (pi+), huge
piercing (pi++), and impaling (imp) damage to x1. Any major
wound (loss of over ½ HP from one blow) cripples the limb.
Damage beyond that threshold is lost. If holding a shield,
double the penalty to hit: -4 for shield arm instead of -2.

Reduce the wounding multiplier of large piercing (pi+), huge
piercing (pi++), and impaling (imp) damage to x1. Any major
wound (loss of over ½ HP from one blow) cripples the limb.
Damage beyond that threshold is lost.

If holding a shield, double the penalty to hit: -8 for
shield hand instead of -4. Reduce the wounding multiplier of
large piercing (pi+), huge piercing (pi++), and impaling
(imp) damage to x1. Any major wound (loss of over ⅓ HP
from one blow) cripples the extremity. Damage beyond that
threshold is lost.

Reduce the wounding multiplier of large piercing (pi+), huge
piercing (pi++), and impaling (imp) damage to x1. Any major
wound (loss of over ⅓ HP from one blow) cripples the
extremity. Damage beyond that threshold is lost.

An attack that misses by 1 hits the torso instead. Neck and
throat. Increase the wounding multiplier of crushing (cr)
and corrosion (cor) attacks to x1½, and that of cutting
(cut) damage to x2. At the GM’s option, anyone killed by a
cutting (cut) blow to the neck is decapitated!

An attack that misses by 1 hits the torso instead. Heart,
lungs, kidneys, etc. Increase the wounding modifier for an
impaling (imp) or any piercing (pi-, pi, pi+, pi++) attack
to x3. Increase the wounding modifier for a tight-beam
burning (burn) attack to x2. Other attacks cannot target the
vitals.

traits.name: Alternate Form
traits.local_notes: Werewolf. Transformation takes 1 sec. Uncontrollable during the full moon.

modifiers.name: Absorptive Change
modifiers.local_notes: @Level of Absorptive Change. 1 None, 2, Light, 3, Medium, 4, Heavy, 5, Extra Heavy@

traits.name: Animal Empathy
traits.local_notes: When you meet an animal, the GM rolls against your IQ and tells you what you “feel.” This reveals the beast’s emotional state and whether it is under supernatural control.

modifiers.name: People Affected
modifiers.local_notes: Almost everyone except @large class of people@

features.situation: from others aware of your reputation
on all IQ rolls to wake up or to recover from surprise or mental stun
to initiative rolls for your side (+2 if you are the leader)

traits.name: Curious
traits.local_notes: Make a self-control roll (CR:12) when presented with an interesting item or situation. On a failure, you engage even if you know it could be dangerous.

traits.name: Guilt Complex
traits.local_notes: You feel responsible for those who play a significant role in your life.

traits.name: High Pain Threshold
traits.local_notes: Never suffer shock penalties when injured.

features.situation: on all HT rolls to avoid knockdown and stunning

modifiers.name: @Rare: Acceleration, Altitude Sickness, Bends, Seasickness, Space Sickness, Nanomachines, etc.@
+8 to all HT rolls to resist
+3 to all HT rolls to resist

traits.name: Infectious Attack
traits.local_notes: Anyone you injure must roll 3d. If they roll under the amount of injury, they are infected.

traits.name: Loner
traits.local_notes: Make a self-control roll (CR:12) whenever anyone lingers nearby, watches over your shoulder, etc. If you fail, you lash out as if you had Bad Temper.

traits.name: Luck
traits.local_notes: Usable once per hour of play.

traits.name: Lunacy
traits.local_notes: During the full moon, you are extremely emotional and volatile; on nights of the new moon you are very passive. While the moon is waxing, you are focused and pleasant; while it is waning, you are apathetic and a little touchy.

features.situation: to all Will and self-control rolls during the full moon

traits.name: Nightmares
traits.local_notes: Make a self-control roll (CR:12) each morning. If you fail, you suffered nightmares; this costs 1 FP that you can only recover through sleep. On a roll of 17 or 18, you are left shaking, and are at -1 to all skill and Perception rolls for the entire day.

traits.name: Post-Combat Shakes
traits.local_notes: Make a self-control roll (CR:12) at the end of any battle. If you fail, roll 3d + the margin of failur, and look up the result on the Fright Check Table.

traits.name: Regeneration
traits.local_notes: Recover 1 HP per minute. Bane: silver.

modifiers.name: Directional
modifiers.local_notes: @Direction: Back, Right, Left, Top or Underside@

modifiers.name: Know Your Own Strength Pricing Variant
